<FONT CLASS="ArticleHead"><BIG>What if they held a war and nobody came?</BIG></FONT>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </FONT><FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthor">Kohath</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleTime>07/09/2001 01:39 AM CDT</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleText>
Their leader is Sssornito (a.k.a. Sssorn), retired boss mob of <a href="http://www.guildparadigm.org">Paradigm</a>.  Their objective is Tunare, Mother of All and one of 5 or 6 unkilled uber-mobs in the game.  Their fight has been dubbed the <a href="http://209.202.194.157/wwwthreads/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=general&amp;Number=273153&amp;page=0&amp;view=expanded&amp;sb=5">MOTHER OF ZERGS vs. MOTHER NATURE</a>, and the time was Saturday at 2PM EST.<p>General Sssornito's organizational efforts were vast, painstaking, and meticulous.  <a href="http://209.202.194.157/wwwthreads/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=general&amp;Number=272683&amp;page=1&amp;view=expanded&amp;sb=5">More than 170</a> level 56+ players, volunteers all, enlisted individually by name.  Commanding officers were appointed, battalions were formed, and specialized squadrons were created to fill specific roles in the master plan.<p>But the preparations didn't end there.  Intelligence reports were gathered and used to produce <a href="http://www.rederon.com/TunareJPeg.jpg">maps</a>.  Troops were outfitted with <a href="http://209.202.194.157/wwwthreads/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=general&amp;Number=272868&amp;page=0&amp;view=expanded&amp;sb=5">special equipment</a> their leaders deemed necessary to wage a successful fight.  A battle plan was <a href="http://209.202.194.157/wwwthreads/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=general&amp;Number=273153&amp;page=0&amp;view=expanded&amp;sb=5">written</a> and the troops were briefed with the details.<p>Perparation was complete and the force watched in anticipation as the moments ticked slowly by, each minute bringing the battle just a little bit closer...<p>As H-hour arrived, it became clear that, of 170 confirmed enlistees, <a href="http://209.202.194.157/wwwthreads/showthreaded.pl?Cat=&amp;Board=general&amp;Number=273528&amp;page=0&amp;view=expanded&amp;sb=5">only 75 showed up</a>.  The battle was cancelled, and Tunare remains, as ever, unharmed.<p>Ssornito might have seen this coming.  In the early 50s BCE, <a href="http://www.athenapub.com/caesarg1.htm">Rome's conquest of Gaul</a> met only scattered resistence. Even though Caesar was far from home and outnumbered by the Celts, the Celtic peoples' inter-tribal conflicts and loose leadership by local cheiftains left them unable to field a force of sufficient size and organization to challenge the efficient Roman legions.<p>Similar factors reigned on Solusek Ro Saturday afternoon.  Sssornito's force was comprised of individuals from a large number of different guilds.  Unfortunately, these guilds had scheduled a number of events for the same Saturday, at the same time.  In far too many cases, Ssornito's troops chose to attend their guild events and failed to report for the Tunare raid.<p>Ssornito has a great task ahead of him before the campaign against Tunare can continue. Like <a href="http://itsa.ucsf.edu/~snlrc/britannia/miscellanea/vercingetorix.html">Vercingetorix</a> did at <a href="http://www.athenapub.com/alesia2.htm">Alesia</a> in 52 BCE, Ssornito must unite the clan leaders in a common purpose, to bring their armies together into a unified fighting force.  Only then can that force attempt another assault on Tunare.  We can only hope that Sssornito has more success against Tunare than <a href="http://www.vercingetorix-lefilm.com/index2.html">Vercingetorix did</a> against Julius Caesar.
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
